Richest WWE Referees in 2024 and their current salary

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Aug 10, 2024, 18:57 (IST)

The salaries of WWE referees varied significantly based on their experience. Senior referees like Chad Patton, Charles Robinson, and Dan Engler earned up to $250,000 annually, while newer referees earned between $50,000 and $80,000 per year. Additionally, match fees varied, with new referees earning $500-$800 per match and experienced ones up to $6000 per match.

9-time Nagaland MLA Noke Wangnao passes away at 87

TNN / Aug 29, 2023, 09:08 (IST)

Nine-time MLA and senior-most serving member in the Nagaland assembly, Noke Wangnao, passed away at the Christian Institute of Health Sciences and Research at Chumukedimaon Monday morning. He was 87.

Kiren Rijiju appointed BJP in-charge for Mizoram polls

TNN / Oct 14, 2023, 06:38 (IST)

The BJP on Friday appointed Union minister Kiren Rijiju as the party's election in-charge for Mizoram where assembly polls will be held on November 7. BJP national secretary Anil Antony and Nagaland deputy chief minister Yanthungo Patton will serve as the party's co-in-charges for the elections in Mizoram, the party said in a statement.

Five dead after heavy rains in eastern China, crops damaged in northeast

Reuters / Jul 23, 2023, 11:45 (IST)

Five people died and two were missing, after heavy rain burst a river bank in a village near eastern China's Hangzhou city on Saturday, flooding houses and carrying away people and their belongings, state media reported. Muddy water gushed through streets in a village in Dayuan township, pouring into houses and turning over cars, pictures published by the Beijing Youth Daily showed.

NSCN-K cadre guns down 'girlfriend', held with accomplice

TNN / May 10, 2023, 13:02 (IST)

An MA final-year student succumbed to a gunshot injury after she was allegedly shot at by her 'boyfriend', a self-styled NSCN-K (Khango) deputy kilonser (minister), Thingiu Khiam (36). The accused and his self-styled bodyguard, Mongchon Khiam (37), have been arrested in this connection.

Northeast Diary: Oil’s not well in Nagaland, and the reason is…

TNN / May 06, 2023, 11:37 (IST)

In Nagaland, everything boils down to one thing – the vexed Naga political issue. Needless to say, the impasse in the Naga peace process has been a hindrance to the overall development of the northeastern state.

Nagaland not to explore oil in disputed areas

TNN / May 06, 2023, 08:30 (IST)

After protests from various quarters, including NSCN (IM), the Nagaland government has decided not to go ahead with plans to facilitate resumption of oil exploration in the disputed areas with Assam without consulting all stakeholders and tribal bodies of the area.

Nagaland sets up panel to improve policing in state

TNN / May 05, 2023, 10:47 (IST)

The state government has set up a high-level committee, headed by DGP Rupin Sharma, to restructure and reorganise the Nagaland Police so as to make it more efficient on functional and operational lines.

Sharad Pawar's NCP decides not to sit in opposition in Nagaland, accepts Neiphiu Rio's leadership

ANI / Mar 08, 2023, 20:55 (IST)

In a major political development, Nationalist Congress Party chief Sharad Pawar has decided that his party will not play the role of opposition in Nagaland and it accepts the leadership of Chief Minister Neiphiu Rio in the state where BJP is NDPP's ally.

NDPP leader Neiphiu Rio takes oath as chief minister of Nagaland for fifth time

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Mar 07, 2023, 14:39 (IST)

Neiphiu Rio was sworn in as the fifth chief minister of Nagaland on Tuesday. Rio won the Northern Angami-II Assembly constituency, trouncing Seyievilie Sachu of the Congress by a mammoth margin of 15,824 votes. He bagged a total of 17,045 votes, which comes to 92.87 per cent of the total votes polled in the seat.

Beef is our staple food, BJP does not interfere: Nagaland deputy CM Patton

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Feb 26, 2023, 11:41 (IST)

BJP leader and Nagaland deputy chief minister Yanthungo Patton says Christians, who constitute more than 85 per cent of the state’s population, will overwhelmingly vote for the national party as they had done in 2018 because they admire Prime Minister Narendra Modi and the development works his government has accomplished in the state and entire Northeast.

Congress: BJP will wipe out every regional party in Nagaland

TNN / Jan 28, 2023, 11:49 (IST)

AICC media coordinator Sujata Paul lashed out at BJP on Friday saying it will wipe out every regional party in Nagaland. Addressing media persons at the Congress Bhavan here, Paul held Neiphiu Rio responsible for the state Nagaland is in today, calling him a "corrupt" and "weak" CM. Paul said the opposition-less government in Nagaland has failed to solve the problems of the state in the last five years.

General Patton for feature event

TNN / Jun 18, 2022, 08:12 (IST)

The Arjun Mangalorkar-trained General Patton is likely to garner maximum support in the D Kumara Siddanna Memorial Trophy, the feature event of the summer races to be run over a sprint here on Saturday.First race at 2pm.1. Treasure Girl Plate (Div-II) 1200M: Tifanny 1, Ansaldo 2. 2.
